commit.message:
Throw NullPointerException for null arguments in Args

The common approach for the past years have been to throw NPE if a null
argument has been passed. This mimics the behavior of
Objects#requireNonNull().
HTTPCORE-595: tolerate NPE thrown by com.android.org.conscrypt.NativeCrypto#SSL_get_shutdown in Android Conscript
HTTPCORE-582: Fixed NPE in SingleCoreIOReactor#processEvents
Fixed NPE in async reverse proxy example
Bugfix: fixed NPE caused by null timeout attribute of IOSessionRequest

Avoid potential NPE.
